column5: Went out from JP. Rented a Hank Heyik hut... got skunked targeting lkers and whities.. minnow/spreaders and half/half williams...  Consolation: everyone els around us got skunked!  Gorgeous day otherwise... good times
The way it goes.. did he drive you out in the Bombardier?

Got skunked too, from Dave's huts. Others got skunked too. A few got 1 to 4 fish, but only a few.  I marked fish throughout the day, not a lot but a decent amount. Many chased my spoon between 3 and 8 feet, the turned back. Happened on four occasions.  Interesting thing, the ice was cracking all day long which tested the nerves of many. On the way back there was a huge crack line near shore on the north side of Georgina Island that loosened up a car sized slab of ice. Luckily Dave's guys are very conscious and noticed the crack before driving over it and marked it off. It went from one end almost to the other. Any unlucky vehicle would have went in if they didn't see it first. It was bad enough that we had to walk to shore.
I got the big skunk today also !!! wicked day to be on the ice
even up here it was a slow day! I only got one laker about 1 1/2 lbs lol
